The article is a letter from former President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President Pro Tempore of the Senate. In the letter, Obama informs them that approximately 90 U.S. Armed Forces personnel have been deployed to Cameroon with the consent of the Government of Cameroon. This deployment is in preparation for additional U.S. forces to conduct intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance operations in the region. The total number of U.S. military personnel expected to be deployed is around 300. Obama states that he directed this deployment in order to further U.S. national security and foreign policy interests, and in accordance with his constitutional authority as Commander in Chief. He provides this report as part of his effort to keep Congress fully informed, as required by the War Powers Resolution. Obama expresses his appreciation for Congress' support in this action.